{"title_page": "Michel Robin", "text_new": "{{short description|French actor}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{Infobox person\n| image        =\n| name         = Michel Robin\n| birth_date   = {{Birth date and age|1930|10|13|df=yes}}\n| birth_place  = [[Reims]], France\n| death_date   =\n| death_place  =\n| occupation   = Actor<br>Comedian\n| yearsactive  = 1966\u2013present\n}}\n\n'''Michel Robin''' (born 13 October 1930) is a French film actor and comedian.<ref name=\"comedie-francaise\">{{Cite web |url=http://www.comedie-francaise.fr/comedien.php?&id=512&idcom=495 |title=Michel Robin |accessdate=28 March 2013 |work=comedie-francaise |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150525190419/http://www.comedie-francaise.fr/comedien.php?&id=512&idcom=495 |archivedate=25 May 2015  }}</ref> He has appeared in 120 films since 1966.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.allocine.fr/personne/fichepersonne-2500/filmographie/ |title=Michel Robin |work=Allocine |accessdate=22 November 2019}}</ref>\n\nHe has worked with directors including [[William Klein (photographer)|William Klein]], [[Costa-Gavras]], [[Marcel Camus]], [[G\u00e9rard Oury]], [[Andrzej \u017bu\u0142awski]], [[Jean L'H\u00f4te]], [[Francis Veber]], [[Jos\u00e9 Giovanni]], [[Claude Chabrol]], [[Alexandre Astruc]], [[Jim Henson]], [[Jaco Van Dormael]], [[\u00c9douard Molinaro]], [[Pascal Thomas]], [[Jean-Paul Salom\u00e9]], [[Jean-Pierre Mocky]], [[Jean-Pierre Jeunet]], [[Sylvain Chomet]], [[Beno\u00eet Jacquot]], [[Alain Resnais]] and [[Arnaud Desplechin]].\n\n==Filmography==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! Director\n! class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n|-\n| rowspan=1|1966\n| ''[[Who Are You, Polly Maggoo?]]''\n| \n| [[William Klein (photographer)|William Klein]]\n| \n|-\n| rowspan=1|1967\n| ''L'une et l'autre''\n| \n| [[Ren\u00e9 Allio]]\n| \n|-\n| rowspan=4|1968\n| ''Les secrets de la mer rouge''\n| The bailiff\n| \n| TV Series (1 Episode)\n|-\n| ''Les dossiers de l'