{{short description|French actor}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2018}}\n{{Infobox person\n| image        =\n| name         = Michel Robin\n| birth_date   = {{Birth date and age|1930|10|13|df=yes}}\n| birth_place  = [[Reims]], France\n| death_date   =\n| death_place  =\n| occupation   = Actor<br>Comedian\n| yearsactive  = 1966\u2013present\n}}\n\n'''Michel Robin''' (born 13 October 1930) is a French film actor and comedian.<ref name=\"comedie-francaise\">{{Cite web |url=http://www.comedie-francaise.fr/comedien.php?&id=512&idcom=495 |title=Michel Robin |accessdate=28 March 2013 |work=comedie-francaise |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150525190419/http://www.comedie-francaise.fr/comedien.php?&id=512&idcom=495 |archivedate=25 May 2015  }}</ref> He has appeared in 120 films since 1966.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.allocine.fr/personne/fichepersonne-2500/filmographie/ |title=Michel Robin |work=Allocine |accessdate=22 November 2019}}</ref>\n\nHe has worked with directors including [[William Klein (photographer)|William Klein]], [[Costa-Gavras]], [[Marcel Camus]], [[G\u00e9rard Oury]], [[Andrzej \u017bu\u0142awski]], [[Jean L'H\u00f4te]], [[Francis Veber]], [[Jos\u00e9 Giovanni]], [[Claude Chabrol]], [[Alexandre Astruc]], [[Jim Henson]], [[Jaco Van Dormael]], [[\u00c9douard Molinaro]], [[Pascal Thomas]], [[Jean-Paul Salom\u00e9]], [[Jean-Pierre Mocky]], [[Jean-Pierre Jeunet]], [[Sylvain Chomet]], [[Beno\u00eet Jacquot]], [[Alain Resnais]] and [[Arnaud Desplechin]].\n\n==Filmography==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! Director\n! class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n|-\n| rowspan=1|1966\n| ''[[Who Are You, Polly Maggoo?]]''\n| \n| [[William Klein (photographer)|William Klein]]\n| \n|-\n| rowspan=1|1967\n| ''L'une et l'autre''\n| \n| [[Ren\u00e9 Allio]]\n| \n|-\n| rowspan=4|1968\n| ''Les secrets de la mer rouge''\n| The bailiff\n| \n| TV Series (1 Episode)\n|-\n| ''Les dossiers de l'agence O''\n| Barbet\n| Jean Salvy, [[Marc Simenon]]\n| TV Series (12 Episodes)\n|-\n| ''L'astragale''\n| Pierre\n| Guy Casaril\n| \n|-\n| ''Les grandes esp\u00e9rances''\n| The postilion\n| Marcel Cravenne\n| TV Movie\n|-\n| rowspan=2|1969\n| ''D\u00e9lire \u00e0 deux''\n| The neighbor\n| [[Michel Mitrani]]\n| TV Movie\n|-\n| ''Caf\u00e9 du square''\n| \n| [[Louis Daquin]]\n| TV Series (2 Episodes)\n|-\n| rowspan=6|1970\n| ''[[The Confession (1970 film)|The Confession]]''\n| The accuser\n| [[Costa-Gavras]]\n| \n|-\n| ''[[Irm\u00e3os Coragem]]''\n| Alberto\n| \n| TV Series (1 Episode)\n|-\n| ''Un otage''\n| The volunteer of I.R.A.\n| Marcel Cravenne (2)\n| TV Movie\n|-\n| ''Le mur de l'Atlantique''\n| The shoemaker\n| [[Marcel Camus]]\n| \n|-\n| ''Alice au pays des merveilles''\n| Fantasy-turtle\n| Jean-Christophe Averty\n| TV Movie\n|-\n| ''Brigitte C. Six''\n| \n| Jean-Claude Huisman\n| Short\n|-\n| rowspan=5|1971\n| ''Les nouvelles aventures de Vidocq''\n| Ploche\n| [[Marcel Bluwal]]\n| TV Series (1 Episode)\n|-\n| ''[[Don't Deliver Us from Evil]]''\n| L\u00e9on\n| Jo\u00ebl S\u00e9ria\n| \n|-\n| ''Ubu encha\u00een\u00e9''\n| Pissembock\n| Jean-Christophe Averty (2)\n| TV Movie\n|-\n| ''La coqueluche''\n| The controller\n| Christian-Paul Arrighi\n| \n|-\n| ''Le songe d'une nuit d'\u00e9t\u00e9''\n| Down-and-hunger\n| Jean-Christophe Averty (3)\n| TV Movie\n|-\n| rowspan=3|1972\n| ''Les cent livres des hommes''\n| Tsiganok\n| \n| TV Series (1 Episode)\n|-\n| ''Quelque part quelqu'un''\n| The depressed patient\n| Yannick Bellon\n| \n|-\n| ''Le petit poucet''\n| The woodcutter\n| [[Michel Boisrond]]\n| \n|-\n| rowspan=7|1973\n| ''La porteuse de pain''\n| Firmin\n| [[Marcel Camus]] (2)\n| TV Mini-Series (1 Episode)\n|-\n| ''L'affaire Dominici''\n| Perrin\n| Claude Bernard-Aubert\n| \n|-\n| ''Wielka milosc Balzaka''\n| \n| Wojciech Solarz\n| TV Mini-Series\n|-\n| ''[[The Invitation (1973 film)|The Invitation]]''\n| Remy\n| [[Claude Goretta]]\n| \n|-\n| ''Les Mohicans de Paris''\n| Barthelemy\n| [[Gilles Grangier