{"title_page": "Mali (film)", "text_new": "{{short description|2018 film}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = Mali\n| image          = Mali (film).jpg\n| caption        = Film poster\n| director       = [[Antonio Nui\u0107]]\n| producer       = \n| writer         = \n| starring       = [[Vito Dijak]]\n| music          = \n| cinematography = \n| editing        = \n| distributor    = \n| released       = {{film date|2018|7|20|[[Pula Film Festival|Pula FF]]|df=yes}}\n| runtime        = 90 minutes\n| country        = Croatia\n| language       = Croatian\n| budget         = \n}}\n\n'''''Mali''''' is a 2018 Croatian [[drama film]] directed by [[Antonio Nui\u0107]]. It was selected as the Croatian entry for the [[Academy Award for Best International Feature Film|Best International Feature Film]] at the [[92nd Academy Awards]], but it was not nominated.<ref name=\"Croatia\">{{cite web|url=https://www.total-croatia-news.com/lifestyle/38225-antonio-nuic |title=\"Mali\" by Antonio Nui\u0107 Croatian Candidate for Oscar |work=Total Croatia |date=3 September 2019 |accessdate=3 September 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Plot==\nFrenki, a drug dealer recently released from prison, battles for custody of his son.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/oscars-croatia-selects-mali-international-feature-category-1236325 |title=Oscars: Croatia Selects 'Mali' for International Feature Category |first=Vladimir |last=Koslov |work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]] |date=3 September 2019 |accessdate=3 September 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Cast==\n* [[Vito Dijak]] as Mali\n* [[Franjo Dijak]] as Frenki\n* [[Hrvoje Keckes]] as Keco\n* [[Bojan Navojec]] as Boki\n* [[Rakan Rushaidat]] as Goc\n\n==See also==\n* [[List of submissions to the 92nd Academy Awards for Best International Feature Film]]\n* [[List of Croatian submissions for the Academy Award for Best International Feature Film]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{IMDb title|7991628|Mali}}\n\